4.57/5  rDev +3.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Bottled 3/14/17, enjoy by date 4/21/17, actually enjoyed on 4/25/17.  Poured into an oversize wine glass.
Pours clear golden without much haze, no sediment.  A 1-inch foamy head that dissipated fairly quickly.
Smell is of fresh and pungent hops strong in grapefruit rind, citrus, tangerine, some peach, and a little bit of spice (clove?) and pine.  Taste follows the nose and is more citrusy up front, then mid-palate has some grapefruit and other fruits with a combination of bitterness and sweetness, and there is a resinous and oily quality whereby it crawls into every part of the mouth supplying different notes in different places.  Feels fairly full bodied with low carbonation.  Sharply bitter in the back of the throat and finishes dry but doesn't linger too much, and somehow invites another gulp.  Incredibly drinkable at 9.4% alcohol.  I loved it. 859 charactersPlinyMeNow, Apr 26, 2017
