4.48/5  rDev +1.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.522 oz. Bomber
Enjoy By: 04.20.17
Bottled CA: 03/14/17
Pours a very nice slightly hazy golden yellow color, very nice carbonation, with a very nice one-finger thick/creamy off-white head, which leaves some very nice sticky lacing behind. The nose is hoppy, with some very nice citrus/pine notes. The taste is very nice, hoppy, with a very nice citrus/pine notes, with some very nice sweetness. Medium body, with a nice dry/bitter finish, ABV is hidden very well. Overall, this is my third Enjoy By, and all have been very tasty.
22 oz. Bomber
Enjoy By: 07.04.16
Bottled On: 05/30/16
Pours a very nice slightly hazy golden yellow color, very nice carbonation, with a very nice one-finger thick/creamy off-white head, which leaves some very nice sticky lacing behind. The nose is hoppy, with some very nice citrus/pine notes. The taste is very nice, hoppy, with a very nice citrus/pine notes, with some very nice sweetness.  Medium body, with a nice dry/bitter finish, ABV is hidden very well.  Overall, this is my second Enjoy By, and both have been very tasty.
22 oz. Bomber
