3.36/5  rDev -23.6%look: 3.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 2.5 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 322oz. bottle split into two snifters.
A - Poured an opaque ambery yellow, thin, short head.
S - The most aromatic brew I've ever laid nose on. Promises of dark fruit, citrus, and wonderful flora entice...
T - ...and totally disappoint. The rich fruit is a little present on the front but is quickly smashed by a bomb of hop flavor and bitterness. I mean "bomb" as in a messy, directionless explosion. Residual bitterness is extreme, and almost seems to step on each successive sip.
M - Certainly not bad. Not too aggressive - it lets the hop presence take care of that.
O - Maybe my taste for hops is underdeveloped, but the extreme bitterness really takes away from the hop flavor here. If it tasted like it smelled, this would be incredible. 748 charactersstompilator, Apr 12, 2015
