This is hands down by far the best beer I have had from Stone. An absolutely delicious double IPA! A beautiful golden brew that just glows in the light. Fantastic clarity and a nice white head. Showing a good amount of carbonation some pretty steady bubble streams. The aroma of this beer screams hops. Very resiny hoppy aroma kinda skunky but it's absolutely bloody brilliant. The taste goes right along with the nose. This is just a delicious hop bomb with tons and tons of hop presence but it's not excessively bitter. My kind of beer. This is delicious hop nectar.
Edit: This was so good I went out and bought another.. Second one wasn't cold when i bought it but at $6 a bottle it seemed like a steal. Tasted like soapy shit. Moral of the story this thing spoils quick way before the enjoy by date if its not cold. Plus, when this brew goes bad it goes really really fucking bad! Had the second one on 11-18-13 and it had already spoiled (12-13-13 IPA). 984 charactersCA_brewster, Nov 17, 2013
